Correctness checks and NT5 preflight attempts:
- recompute $n,\sigma(n),\tau(n)$; confirm $\gcd(\sigma(n),n)=5$ and solvability of the congruence;
- solve the reduced congruence modulo $n/5$ and apply the $v_{19}(x)=1$ filter to obtain $x_0$ and $x_0\bmod 1000$;
- "NT5: small-mod-only attacks (mods in {2,3,4,5,7,8,9,11}), bounded scan up to 100000, and a wrong-branch/template guess check."

Correctness checks: compute $b=p^{k}q+1$ and the predicted $t=p^{k}q$; verify $b^{t}\equiv 1\pmod{p^{2k}q^{2}}$ via modular exponentiation and confirm minimality by checking all proper divisors of $t$.
Carry checks: compute $S_b(X),S_b(Y),S_b(X+Y)$ from the closed-form digit descriptions and confirm $S_b(X)+S_b(Y)-S_b(X+Y)=(b-1)C$ matches carry simulation.
NT5 preflight attempts (all failed to recover the true $N$ without the intended kernel):
(a) small-mod-only attack: replace the true modulus with mods in {2,3,4,5,7,8,9,11}, compute cycle lengths and their lcm to guess an exponent, producing an incorrect $N$;
(b) tiny bounded scan: search exponents $t\le 20000$ for $b^{t}\equiv 1\pmod{p^{2k}q^{2}}$ and find none;
(c) template fits: sample multiple admissible $(p,q,k)$ and check that $N\bmod 1000$ is not constant, does not satisfy any affine template $N\equiv a(t\bmod 1000)+c\pmod{1000}$, and is not determined by $k\bmod r$ for any period $1\le r\le 6$.
